From 1fad0a28fb70a50ef42701f2556f8fd6b7050b43 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?J=C3=B6rg=20Thalheim?= <joerg@thalheim.io>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 09:15:16 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] wifi: iwlwifi: pcie: mark transport dead when device
 falls off the bus
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

When the AX210 firmware crashes and the device drops off the PCIe bus
(all CSR reads return 0xffffffff), every register access in
_iwl_trans_pcie_grab_nic_access() busy-polls CSR_GP_CNTRL for 15ms
before timing out. Code paths such as the firmware error dump
(iwl_fw_dbg_collect_sync) and the stop-device flow perform thousands
of such accesses, often under RTNL via mac80211 drv_start(). This
stalls the system for minutes, blocks every netlink user
(NetworkManager, wpa_supplicant, syncthing, ...) and triggers hung
task warnings, leaving a hard reboot as the only way out.

The driver already detects this condition (cntrl == ~0U) but only
acts on it when the remove_when_gone module parameter is set. Set
STATUS_TRANS_DEAD unconditionally in this case so that all subsequent
register accesses fail fast instead of repeatedly polling dead
hardware. remove_when_gone behavior is unchanged: it additionally
schedules the PCIe remove/rescan.

Observed on Framework Laptop (AMD) with AX210 [8086:2725, rev 1a],
firmware 89.735b75a4.0, kernel 7.0.8; same signature reported in
kernel bugzilla 221251, 221178 and 220988.

Signed-off-by: Jörg Thalheim <joerg@thalheim.io>
---
 .../intel/iwlwifi/pcie/gen1_2/trans.c         | 24 +++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/gen1_2/trans.c b/drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/gen1_2/trans.c
index 4560d92d76fe0..37df3e940327f 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/gen1_2/trans.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/gen1_2/trans.c
@@ -2390,12 +2390,28 @@ bool _iwl_trans_pcie_grab_nic_access(struct iwl_trans *trans, bool silent)
 
 		iwl_trans_pcie_dump_regs(trans, trans_pcie->pci_dev);
 
-		if (iwlwifi_mod_params.remove_when_gone && cntrl == ~0U)
-			iwl_trans_pcie_reset(trans,
-					     IWL_RESET_MODE_REMOVE_ONLY);
-		else
+		if (cntrl == ~0U) {
+			/*
+			 * The device fell off the PCIe bus: every register
+			 * access will time out after 15ms of busy-polling.
+			 * Code paths such as the firmware error dump perform
+			 * thousands of register accesses, possibly under RTNL
+			 * (e.g. mac80211 drv_start), stalling the whole
+			 * system for minutes and triggering hung task
+			 * warnings in unrelated tasks. Mark the transport
+			 * dead so that all subsequent accesses fail fast.
+			 */
+			IWL_ERR(trans,
+				"Device gone from bus, marking transport dead\n");
+			if (iwlwifi_mod_params.remove_when_gone)
+				iwl_trans_pcie_reset(trans,
+						     IWL_RESET_MODE_REMOVE_ONLY);
+			else
+				set_bit(STATUS_TRANS_DEAD, &trans->status);
+		} else {
 			iwl_write32(trans, CSR_RESET,
 				    CSR_RESET_REG_FLAG_FORCE_NMI);
+		}
 
 		spin_unlock(&trans_pcie->reg_lock);
 		return false;
-- 
